The paper deals with the construction of abstractions for stochastic control systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of temporal logic specifications and policy synthesis, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper proposes a computational scheme for constructing abstractions, which involves mathematical optimization and numerical methods, making it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO).
